SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1039
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to honor the 3rd Annual Tennessee Small Band
Association State Championship.
WHEREAS, for decades, Tennessee marching band state championships were divided
into three levels: the Division I state championship, the Division II state championship, and the
Contest of Champions at Middle Tennessee State University; and
WHEREAS, the Tennessee Secondary School Athletic Association (TSSAA) allows five
classes in volleyball; six classes in basketball, baseball, and softball; and nine classes in
football; and
WHEREAS, there is a need for a marching band state championship for public schools
with very small marching bands; and
WHEREAS, in 2022, several public schools joined forces and established the
Tennessee Small Band Association (TSBA) and the TSBA Celebration marching championship
to represent public schools in the Great State of Tennessee with enrollment of 500 students or
fewer, according to TSSAA enrollment figures, and with marching bands of thirty or fewer wind
and percussion instruments, with the physical awards for such championships now known as
the Senate Trophy; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those estimable teachers who have dedicated their time and energies to educating
their students and providing scholarships and competitive opportunities for students in
secondary schools around the State; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor the Watertown High School Band and
SJR1039
016946
- 1 -

Band Director Scott Corley for hosting the 3rd Annual Tennessee Small Band Association State
Championship on November 1, 2025, congratulate sixth-place band Jo Byrns High School and
Director Dawson Campbell, fifth-place band Trousdale County High School and Director Robert
A. Joines II, fourth-place band Perry County High School and Director Marlana Nyholt, third-
place band East Hickman High School and Director Greg Gunther, TSBA State Champion
Soloist Kalani Joyner and second-place band Hollow-Rock Bruceton High School and Director
Keith Breeden, and TSBA State Champion and winner of the Senate Trophy Gordonsville High
School Band and Director Tiffanii Brown, and extend to them our best wishes for much
continued success in all their future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
